TY  - JOUR
AU  - Barron, Daniel
AU  - Guo, Yingni
AU  - Reich, Bryony
T1  - Wealth Dynamics in Communities
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdac057
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 4
SP  - 1642
EP  - 1668
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This article develops a model to explore how favour exchange influences wealth dynamics. We identify a key obstacle to wealth accumulation: wealth crowds out favour exchange. Therefore, households must choose between growing their wealth and accessing favour exchange. We show that low-wealth households rely on favour exchange at the cost of having tightly limited long-term wealth. As a result, initial wealth disparities persist and can even grow worse. We then explore how communities and policymakers can overcome this obstacle. Using simulations, we show that community benefits and place-based policies can stimulate both saving and favour exchange, and in some cases, can even transform favour exchange into a force that accelerates wealth accumulation.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdac057
ER  - 



