AB  - This is a correction to: David Berger, Ian Dew-Becker, Stefano Giglio, Uncertainty Shocks as Second-Moment News Shocks, The Review of Economic Studies, Volume 87, Issue 1, January 2020, Pages 40–76, https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdz010The published version of this paper has a typo in the description of the data. The reported analysis uses manufacturing employment, following Bloom (2009), rather than employment for the full economy. Results using total employment are qualitatively identical and quantitatively highly similar, and a full version of the tables and figures using total private employment is available on request from the authors.
